        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 6:25PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 625 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 9 miles north of Gilmer to
near Gladewater. Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Diana, Warren City, Holly Springs, Daingerfield, Jenkins, Lafayette,
Ore City, West Mountain, Center Point, Harleton, Union Grove, East
Mountain, Lone Star, Cedar Springs, Hughes Springs, Avinger,
Gladewater, Clarksville City, White Oak, and Longview.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for northeastern
Texas.</instruction>
